Features
--------

The cb2db is a ndo2db replacement. It has the following features :

 - configurable log output
 - multi instance input
 - multi socket input
 - multi output
 - TLS on input possible
 - lower network footprint
 - smaller DB load
 - optimized DB schema
 - written in C++ for more stability
 - fully configurable
 - multi-threaded (make use of modern processors)


cb2db uses some external projects to provide those features :

 - GNU TLS to provide TLS connection between the broker and cb2db
 - Boost as this C++ library provide a good abstraction layer and is really
   powerful
 - MySQL C Connector to handle MySQL databases
 - libpq to handle PostgreSQL databases
